FT  25 APR 92 / Finance &amp; the Family: Correction
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Weekend FT front page article on the Daily Telegraph on February 20 said
that Mr Conrad Black bought control of the group for Pounds 30m. We should
make it clear that after Mr Black bought a 14 per cent stake for Pounds 10m
in May 1985, as the article explained, he later acquired control via
diluting rights issues.
