FT  25 APR 92 / Volkswagen falls out with Yanase
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Volkswagen, the German car maker, has fallen out with its Japanese importer,
Yanase, which said yesterday it would stop handling Volkswagen and Audi
models at the end of the year.
The decision by Yanase threatens to disrupt Volkswagen sales in Japan, where
Volkswagen claims the largest share of imported cars. Volkswagen, however,
has been expanding its own sales outlets. It has also begun to sell through
Toyota dealers and may be in position to bounce back.
Yanase, Japan's biggest imported car dealer, was unhappy at the prospect of
losing its near-exclusive sales of Volkswagen models and will attempt to
replace Volkswagen sales with other cars, possibly from Opel the German
subsidiary of General Motors.
