but it was not feasible to dispatch a UN peace-keeping force to the
strife-torn republic.
In western Bosnia, Croatian radio reported 94 federal soldiers killed in
fighting between Serb and Croat forces. But Tanjug, the Belgrade-based news
agency, said four soldiers had been killed and 50 wounded, and it claimed
Croat forces had suffered far greater losses.
