FT  24 APR 92 / Observer: Boy George
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
When Graeme Gilchrist, Union Discount's former boss, left in February after
unveiling hefty losses, a first stab at mending fences was the arrival, as
joint deputy chairman, of Sir George Blunden, highly respected former deputy
governor of the Bank of England.
Now George Blunden junior, who has been running S G Warburg's discount
operation, turns up as chief executive. Do not assume it was merely the
name.
Central banking relationships have their uses - as John and James, two of
BoE governor Robin Leigh-Pemberton's five sons, respectively at Smith New
Court and Warburgs, would attest. But it seems that Blunden, earlier the
