Kyoseki.
Nippon Mining acquired Gould in 1988.
Nippon Mining expects Gould to post group net losses of Dollars 180m for
1991. Gould's long-term and short-term debts came to Dollars 900m as of the
end of 1991.
Nippon Mining forecasts group pre-tax losses of Y500m (Dollars 3.73m) for
the year ended March, mainly due to Gould's poor performance. It had group
pre-tax profits of Y14.88bn in the previous year.
