<HEADLINE>
FT  24 APR 92 / UK Company News: Hartons losses deepen to Pounds 5.4m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANGUS FOSTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Hartons Group, which through its VT Plastics division distributes plastic
sheet and film, was hard hit by recession in its main markets of the UK and
Europe and announced losses before tax more than doubled from Pounds 2.14m
to Pounds 5.36m in the year to December 31.
Turnover fell to Pounds 92.9m (Pounds 129m) and there was an operating loss
of Pounds 918,000, compared with a profit of Pounds 3.42m in 1990.
Interest charges fell to Pounds 2.99m (Pounds 4.33m) because of reduced
borrowings. But exceptional items of Pounds 1.22m, the cost of further
rationalisation, were unchanged.
The company's North American distribution business was sold in July last
year, leading to an extraordinary loss of Pounds 617,000.
Losses attributable to shareholders totalled Pounds 6.2m (Pounds 2.8m) and
there were losses per share of 8.1p (3.6p).
No dividend is proposed.
</TEXT>
