<HEADLINE>
FT  24 APR 92 / UK Company News: Prestwick returns to the black with interim
Pounds 81,000
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JAMES BUXTON, Scottish Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
PRESTWICK Holdings, the Ayr-based printed circuit board manufacturer, made a
pre-tax profit of Pounds 81,000 in the six months to January 31, compared
with a loss of Pounds 741,000 in the comparable period of 1991.
Turnover rose by 17 per cent to Pounds 13.9m, reflecting increased exports,
mainly to EC countries, and contributions from acquisitions.
Prestwick said that the costs associated with the new acquisitions and the
costs of increasing production in the company's plants at Ayr and Irvine
were being taken in the first half.
'We will continue with our strategy to create a broader-based
interconnection group,' Mr Wayne Osman, chief executive, said. Many of the
elements designed to give the company a significant competitive edge were
now in place.
The interim dividend is maintained at 0.5p, payable from fully diluted
earnings of 0.4p (losses of 2.3p) per share.
