Sir, The professional exporting community welcomes Mr Michael Heseltine's
decision to restore the title president of the board of trade (Observer,
April 21).
For far too long in recent history the 'trade' element of the Department of
Trade and Industry has been treated as the Cinderella sector. International
trade is vital to the UK's economy. Unless we reverse the current disastrous
balance of payments deficit, sterling's weakness and high interest rates
will persist indefinitely.
