Commission played down the effects of the fallout.
The new government of independent Ukraine has made an effort to come clean
about the effects of Chernobyl and vowed to shut down the reactor. One of
Ukraine's leading environmental activists, Mr Yuri Shcherbak, has been named
as environment minister.
